NAME
    Number::Base::SpreadsheetColumn - Convert spreadsheet column name (e.g.
    "A", "Z", "AA") to number (e.g. 0, 25, 26) and vice versa

VERSION
    This document describes version 0.001 of Number::Base::SpreadsheetColumn
    (from Perl distribution Number-Base-SpreadsheetColumn), released on
    2026-02-02.

SYNOPSIS
     use Number::Base::SpreadsheetColumn qw(from_scbase to_scbase);

     say from_scbase("A");  # => 0
     say from_scbase("Z");  # => 25
     say from_scbase("AA"); # => 26
     say from_scbase("AZ"); # => 51
     say from_scbase("BA"); # => 52

     say to_scbase(0);  # => "A"
     say to_scbase(25); # => "Z"
     say to_scbase(26); # => "AA"
     say to_scbase(51); # => "AZ"
     say to_scbase(52); # => "BA"

DESCRIPTION
    Spreadsheet column is basically 26-base number with 1-based index.

FUNCTIONS
  from_scbase
  to_scbase
